</span></div><div class="meta-container " itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><h2 class="title article-title" itemprop="name">
					Playing God: Pandemic Brings Moral Dilemmas to US Hospitals
					
				</h2><div class="deck spacer-top-20 spacer-bottom-15" itemprop="description">Two Christian bioethicists on life or death issues that American doctors may soon face.</div>
<div class="article-byline "><span itemprop="author">Interview by Kara Bettis</span><span class="pipe"></span><span class="postdate" itemprop="datePublished">March 31, 2020</span></div>
<h2 class="title spacer-top-10"></h2></div>
</div>
</div>
</section><section class="article-featured-image "><div class="container"><figure class="p-relative align-center spacer-top-40"><img class="img-responsive" src="https://www-images.christianitytoday.com/images/116396.jpg?w=940" srcset="https://www-images.christianitytoday.com/images/116396.jpg?w=1880 2x" width="940" alt="Playing God: Pandemic Brings Moral Dilemmas to US Hospitals" title="Playing God: Pandemic Brings Moral Dilemmas to US Hospitals" /></figure><figcaption class="spacer-top-5 spacer-bottom-5"><div class="credit ">
									Image:
									
										Illustration by Mallory Rentsch / Source Images: sturti / Getty Images
									</div>
</figcaption></div></section><section class="container"><div class="spacer-top-25 u-cf social-nav-item"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/system/social/styles/share.css?07082014"></link>
				<div
